WEBVTT

00:01.300 --> 00:03.490
Divorce lawyers like to say...

00:03.510 --> 00:08.039
that "love" is the ultimate
unenforceable contract.

00:08.470 --> 00:11.920
It is always being
re-negotiated by time.

00:13.650 --> 00:16.960
Whether it's the love of
a husband for his wife...

00:17.310 --> 00:20.290
or a parent for a child...

00:20.650 --> 00:23.520
or even a lover for their sweetheart...

00:23.550 --> 00:26.300
the day invariably
arises when the contract,

00:26.330 --> 00:31.300
the agreements and understanding
that define a relationship, change.

00:33.140 --> 00:37.830
The function of time, familiarity
or sometimes just Mother Nature.

00:39.440 --> 00:43.690
Well,well,if it isn't our own
Deputy Doll. Back for another test?

00:43.910 --> 00:45.370
I think the last one was defective.

00:45.410 --> 00:49.510
The plus sign looks more like a
division symbol, so I remain unconvinced.

00:54.070 --> 00:55.890
Third test today, Mama Bear.

00:55.910 --> 00:58.550
Your Eggo is preggo; no doubt about it.

00:58.570 --> 01:00.890
Silencio,old man.

01:00.910 --> 01:02.750
You pay for that pee
stick when you're done.

01:02.780 --> 01:06.070
Don't think it's yours just 'cause
you marked it with your urine.

01:11.610 --> 01:50.410
<i><b>Medium
Season 05 - Episode 05
** A Taste of Her Own Medicine **</b></i>

01:58.500 --> 01:59.330
But I don't get it.

01:59.360 --> 02:03.140
Why do I have to go to the doctor's
office when I don't feel sick?

02:03.180 --> 02:06.070
Well,'cause Mommy's working
again and Daddy's working again,

02:06.100 --> 02:08.490
which means we have our insurance back.

02:08.500 --> 02:09.699
So?

02:09.740 --> 02:13.690
So,that means that we can go to the
doctor, and somebody else will pay for it.

02:13.720 --> 02:17.030
Well,tell them to save their
money. We're not interested.

02:17.040 --> 02:18.670
We're all going to do it.

02:18.700 --> 02:20.950
Mommy's going to go see her doctor.

02:20.990 --> 02:24.170
Daddy's going to see
his doctor this morning.

02:24.200 --> 02:26.470
Everybody's going to get a checkup.

02:26.510 --> 02:28.610
Uh-oh,this isn't good.

02:28.650 --> 02:32.310
When they say "checkup,"
they mean shots.

02:32.330 --> 02:36.090
I don't want no, no shot.

02:36.110 --> 02:40.660
Hey now,just 'cause you're going to the doctor for
a checkup doesn't mean you're going to get shots.

02:40.690 --> 02:42.360
Right. And fish can't swim.

02:42.370 --> 02:44.290
I don't want a shot!

02:44.340 --> 02:47.600
Look at your sister,honey.
You're getting her all upset.

02:47.610 --> 02:49.320
Hey,I got an idea.

02:49.350 --> 02:54.220
What if,um,we go to the
doctor's office, and,well...

02:54.240 --> 02:59.710
we get the shots, and
then,afterwards, we go to the toy store

02:59.740 --> 03:03.140
and you guys let us pick
out whatever we want?

03:03.620 --> 03:04.640
What?

03:04.680 --> 03:06.510
Wait a second,where did you get that?

03:06.550 --> 03:08.850
They do it on television.

03:08.880 --> 03:10.570
Actually,I've seen it a lot.

03:10.600 --> 03:14.250
Well,I'm not interested in
talking about television,honey.

03:15.410 --> 03:18.130
I got to go to my doctor's appointment.

03:18.140 --> 03:21.190
Us,too. Us,too.

03:24.420 --> 03:27.140
Got a minute for a friend?

03:27.240 --> 03:28.230
Councilman Leaming...

03:28.280 --> 03:30.850
Don't fire anyone. I told
them not to announce me.

03:30.860 --> 03:32.680
I'm here on unofficial business.

03:32.720 --> 03:34.410
Well,then let me give
you one of these...

03:34.440 --> 03:37.850
unofficially,of course.
Save me a postage stamp.

03:37.860 --> 03:39.350
What the hell's this,Manuel?

03:39.400 --> 03:41.550
A party. It's Lily's idea,actually.

03:41.560 --> 03:44.440
A way to sort of thank everybody
who works here for hanging in there,

03:44.450 --> 03:45.980
keeping the faith while I was gone.

03:46.010 --> 03:48.180
But don't worry,we're
paying for everything.

03:48.220 --> 03:50.700
Not a dime of taxpayers' money.

03:51.880 --> 03:53.870
What's going on,Jimmy?

03:53.910 --> 03:58.040
You know my daughter Meredith-- finally
got married a little more than a year ago.

03:58.050 --> 04:01.650
Nice fella. He has a little
girl with heart trouble.

04:01.660 --> 04:03.320
Actually,that's how they met.

04:03.370 --> 04:06.180
Meredith was the little girl's nurse.

04:06.220 --> 04:11.090
Two days ago she sent my
wife and me this e-mail.

04:11.100 --> 04:14.670
"Dear Mom and Dad,I'm
embarrassed to tell you this,

04:14.680 --> 04:16.610
"but I think,for the
first time in my life,

04:16.649 --> 04:20.149
"I understand what it
means to hit rock bottom.

04:20.180 --> 04:22.870
"I think the only cure
is time and distance.

04:22.900 --> 04:24.500
"I need to get away.

04:24.540 --> 04:27.320
s his isn't forever, it's just for now.

04:27.360 --> 04:31.720
I promise to get in
touch soon. Meredith."

04:33.530 --> 04:35.140
I'm so sorry,Jim.

04:35.160 --> 04:38.190
She sent one to her husband,too.

04:38.230 --> 04:41.230
What can I do? How... can I help you?

04:41.240 --> 04:43.770
Sh She's been gone four days.

04:43.800 --> 04:46.480
My wife,my
son-in-law...

04:46.530 --> 04:50.100
they're convinced that
she's going to come back.

04:50.140 --> 04:54.820
But this is a girl who's never gone more
than 48 hours without calling me or her mother

04:54.830 --> 04:56.790
about some crisis or other.

04:56.830 --> 05:00.520
Did you go to the police?
File a missing persons report?

05:01.170 --> 05:04.690
I don't want to do
that. I'm a councilman.

05:04.700 --> 05:07.940
Her husband's a big shot
over at Phoenix West Bank.

05:07.990 --> 05:09.630
They're going to want to question him.

05:09.660 --> 05:12.400
And then the papers will
get ahold of it... no.

05:12.640 --> 05:16.010
You know,I have a couple of people who work
for me, pretty good at this kind of thing.

05:16.050 --> 05:19.550
And I know I can trust them
to keep it to themselves.

05:19.560 --> 05:21.520
Why don't you let me see what I can do.

05:21.530 --> 05:26.900
Joe. Joe! Joe.

05:27.980 --> 05:30.530
I need you to wake up.

05:30.560 --> 05:32.560
Oh,hey,Doc.

05:32.590 --> 05:35.250
Oh,sorry, must have dozed off.

05:35.280 --> 05:38.770
Yeah,the nurse said she's been
trying to wake you for ten minutes.

05:42.780 --> 05:45.030
Devalos said you wanted to see me.

05:45.070 --> 05:49.330
Yeah,I do indeed. I do indeed.
What's with the funny look?

05:49.340 --> 05:52.960
Nothing. You've just been on
my mind lately. You and Lynn.

05:53.650 --> 05:54.530
Well,how you guys doing?

05:54.570 --> 05:57.530
We're doing... I mean,you
know,to the extent we can.

05:57.540 --> 06:00.220
Haven't you got better
things to think about?

06:00.740 --> 06:03.490
Maybe. Maybe not.

06:03.840 --> 06:05.380
So what's all this?

06:05.430 --> 06:08.100
One of Manny's city
council buddies dropped by.

06:08.110 --> 06:10.620
Daughter ran out on her
husband couple days ago.

06:10.650 --> 06:13.160
Papa's stressing 'cause he
doesn't know where she is.

06:14.550 --> 06:16.830
- Pretty.
- Smart. Went to school.

06:16.840 --> 06:19.280
Started premed,dropped out.

06:19.540 --> 06:23.650
Became a private nurse,
which is when she met hubby.

06:24.000 --> 06:27.530
- Was he sick?
- His little girl. Born with a bad heart.

06:27.540 --> 06:29.480
Waiting for a transplant.

06:29.520 --> 06:32.610
First wife couldn't take
the pressure-- took off.

06:32.930 --> 06:36.570
He finally got divorced
in absentia and,uh...

06:36.580 --> 06:39.980
nursie here,Meredith, took her place.

06:40.010 --> 06:43.300
Anyway,I'm going to do the credit
card,cell phone monitoring thing.

06:43.330 --> 06:47.750
See what she might have spent, where she
might have spent it, who she might have called.

06:48.210 --> 06:51.070
Devalos asked me to put this little
care package together for you in hopes

06:51.100 --> 06:53.170
that you might do that voodoo you do,

06:53.210 --> 06:58.010
but I have a hunch our little wifey just
parked herself in a four-star hotel somewhere.

06:58.020 --> 06:59.710
Nice car.

06:59.740 --> 07:02.870
Daddy's little girl
has to have a nice car.

07:02.880 --> 07:06.860
So Marie,little Marie,
when he gave her her shot,

07:06.870 --> 07:11.400
she smiled,Joe. And Bridgette,whoo.

07:12.270 --> 07:17.500
You would have thought that he was performing
open-heart surgery without anesthesia.

07:18.560 --> 07:21.950
So afterward, I took
them to the toy store.

07:22.360 --> 07:24.090
I'm proud of you.

07:24.120 --> 07:29.170
Not letting your previously held convictions
get in the way of making our children happy.

07:31.290 --> 07:35.490
Now,listen,I got to talk to you about
something that happened at the doctor's office.

07:35.530 --> 07:37.670
What are you talking about?
You told me everything was fine.

07:37.680 --> 07:41.200
Yeah,it is. Well,sort of.

07:41.640 --> 07:46.610
He seemed to think that I have some kind
of a sleep deprivation thing going on.

07:46.650 --> 07:50.940
Doesn't everybody over the age of 12 have
a little sleep deprivation thing going on?

07:50.970 --> 07:54.960
I don't know, he seemed to think that
it was something to be taken seriously.

07:54.970 --> 07:58.410
All right,well,what
would make him think that?

07:58.440 --> 08:02.430
I think he got his first inkling when I
fell asleep in his waiting room this morning.

08:02.440 --> 08:04.210
Oh,my.

08:04.250 --> 08:07.870
The truth is,I am
exhausted all the time.

08:09.310 --> 08:15.810
At first,he wanted to check me into the hospital
one night next week and do a sleep study.

08:16.160 --> 08:19.910
That's where they hook you
up to a computer and they...

08:19.950 --> 08:22.580
they try to figure out
what the problem is.

08:22.630 --> 08:25.240
Then after we... you know,we...

08:25.610 --> 08:29.230
we talked for a little
while, we both realized...

08:33.789 --> 08:36.580
What,you both think this is my fault?

08:36.610 --> 08:40.900
Fault? Nobody mentioned fault.
I didn't use the word "fault."

08:40.909 --> 08:42.679
Okay,what word would you use?

08:42.720 --> 08:44.030
I don't want to use any word.

08:44.070 --> 08:46.840
I think the doctor's just trying
to figure out cause and effect.

08:46.880 --> 08:49.110
I don't think that
fault factors into it.

08:49.140 --> 08:50.420
And I'm the cause.

08:50.460 --> 08:52.830
Okay,look, I wouldn't use
the word "cause" either.

08:52.860 --> 08:54.270
But,Allison,you've got to be realistic.

08:54.340 --> 08:57.770
I mean,you're up once or twice a night,
which means that I'm up once or twice a night.

08:57.800 --> 09:01.310
The problem is,that after you tell me
about your dream I can't get back to sleep.

09:01.370 --> 09:06.610
I sit here and I stare and I wait for the sun
to come up or for you to have another dream.

09:08.940 --> 09:11.960
Okay,so what does he want us to do?

09:11.990 --> 09:14.620
What are we talking
here? Ear plugs,or...

09:14.630 --> 09:16.220
How do we handle this?

09:16.250 --> 09:19.060
I don't want you to be exhausted.

09:19.100 --> 09:22.970
Initially,he wants us
to try sleeping apart.

09:22.990 --> 09:24.260
That's his plan?

09:24.320 --> 09:25.620
Just for a week.

09:25.670 --> 09:27.870
I mean,I think it's more
diagnostic than anything else.

09:27.900 --> 09:29.760
You know,if after a week
I'm feeling better,then...

09:29.770 --> 09:30.910
What?

09:30.950 --> 09:35.070
If after a week you're feeling better--
what? That we'd sleep apart forever?

09:35.080 --> 09:36.870
Doesn't sound like much of a plan.

09:36.900 --> 09:39.030
Well,that's not his
plan, that's your plan.

09:39.060 --> 09:42.840
I mean,I'm sure he's got some kind of
a protocol in mind if this,you know,

09:42.870 --> 09:45.820
in fact,turns out to be the problem.

